  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation</title>

    <para>
      Install libdrm by running the following commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>sed -e "/pthread-stubs/d" -i configure.ac &amp;&amp;
autoreconf -fi &amp;&amp;
./configure --prefix=/usr \
            --enable-udev &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now, as the <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

    <sect3>
      <title>Command Explanations</title>

      <para>
        <command>sed -e "/pthread-stubs/d" -i configure.ac</command>: This sed
        removes dependency on libpthread-stubs package which is useless on
        Linux.
      </para>

      <para>
        <parameter>--enable-udev</parameter>: This option enables support for
        using Udev instead of <command>mknod</command>.
      </para>

    </sect3>

  </sect2>

